Four people died and 18 others were injured in a collision between a truck and a minibus taxi on the N1 close to the Brandfort off-ramp about 20 to 30km from Bloemfontein on Saturday evening, Free State paramedics said. ER24 and other services attended to the accident and found patients scattered across the scene , ER24 spokeswoman Chitra Bodasing-Harduth said. Sadly two people found in the taxi and two who were believed to have been ejected had succumbed to their injuries. One person sustained critical injuries and all others sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate. They were treated and transported to various hospitals. The cause of the accident was unknown, she said.